\begin_layout Standard
When a user has the master data open for any resource other than subjects
 opening the related lesson view automatically opens to the selected resource.
 For example if I have highlighted the class xyz then opening the lessons>classe
s dialogue automatically opens the lessons which are marked for class xyz.
 When the subject master data view is opened and the subject xyz is highlighted
 opening the lessons>subjects view not only does not open to a list of lessons
 instancing that particular subject, it loads a random batch of lessons
 and sets the filter to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Suggesting that these were all the lessons available at all.
 Except for the misleading 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 entry the filter is actually quite empty and doesn't allow for the fast
 filtering to any particular subject.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Descriptions can be filtered to a particular resource type, and when creating
 with this filter activated will be associated with this resource type.
 However, there is no way to associate existing descriptions with resource
 types or to change an existing association of description to resource.
 Additionally as in all other matters the masking of system keys allows
 for no double entries.
 Specifically the use of the description 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Practical Training
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for a subject must out of necessity be the same description which describes
 a lesson.
 This means that this element must be created without a resource association
 to be of use.
\end_layout

